The paper focuses on apprenticeship learning for robots, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The approach proposed in the paper involves fusing temporal information and multimodal data, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions integrating robot perception with decision making, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY).
